    <stitle>STEERING COLUMN ASSEMBLY, TILT/TELESCOPING - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcsubsecinfo>
            <para>The same lever, mounted on the left side of the steering column, is used to actuate both the tilt and
                telescoping modes of the column.
            </para>
        </svcsubsecinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="1">
            <title>TILT</title>
            <para>The adjustable six (6) position steering column assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0500902">Figure 2</hotlnk>) can be moved toward or away from the driver. The tilt
                positions are adjustable in 7-degree increments from 14 degrees above centerline of column to 21 degrees
                below centerline of column. To adjust the column, push the control lever down (away from the steering
                wheel) and move the steering wheel to the desired position. Release the lever to lock the column in
                position.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0500902" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0500902" filename="../figg05/G0500902.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Tilt/Telescoping Steering Wheel Controls</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
